\raisebox{20pt}{B516x512S14021485x488} \raisebox{20pt}{B508x515S11a20493x485} \raisebox{20pt}{B508x508S17620492x492} \raisebox{20pt}{B508x515S10e20493x485} \raisebox{20pt}{B508x508S14a20493x493} \raisebox{20pt}{B508x515S11a20493x485} \raisebox{20pt}{B507x511S14720493x489} \raisebox{20pt}{B508x508S20320493x493}

\begin{multicols}{2}


\begin{center}
\enubox{\bf Chapter 1}
M517x530S15a48484x471S16d40499x475S22b04501x500 M508x515S10000493x485 
\end{center}


\enubox{1 The proverbs of Solomon the son of David, king of Israel;}

\enubox{2 To know wisdom and instruction; to perceive the words of understanding;}

\enubox{3 To receive the instruction of wisdom, justice, and judgment, and equity;}

\enubox{4 To give subtilty to the simple, to the young man knowledge and discretion.}

\enubox{5 A wise man will hear, and will increase learning; and a man of understanding shall attain unto wise counsels:}

\enubox{6 To understand a proverb, and the interpretation; the words of the wise, and their dark sayings.}

\enubox{7 The fear of the LORD is the beginning of knowledge: but fools despise wisdom and instruction.}

\enubox{8 My son, hear the instruction of thy father, and forsake not the law of thy mother:}

\enubox{9 For they shall be an ornament of grace unto thy head, and chains about thy neck.}

\enubox{10 My son, if sinners entice thee, consent thou not.}

\enubox{11 If they say, Come with us, let us lay wait for blood, let us lurk privily for the innocent without cause:}

\enubox{12 Let us swallow them up alive as the grave; and whole, as those that go down into the pit:}

\enubox{13 We shall find all precious substance, we shall fill our houses with spoil:}

\enubox{14 Cast in thy lot among us; let us all have one purse:}

\enubox{15 My son, walk not thou in the way with them; refrain thy foot from their path:}

\enubox{16 For their feet run to evil, and make haste to shed blood.}

\enubox{17 Surely in vain the net is spread in the sight of any bird.}

\enubox{18 And they lay wait for their own blood; they lurk privily for their own lives.}

\enubox{19 So are the ways of every one that is greedy of gain; which taketh away the life of the owners thereof.}

\enubox{20 Wisdom crieth without; she uttereth her voice in the streets:}

\enubox{21 She crieth in the chief place of concourse, in the openings of the gates: in the city she uttereth her words, saying,}

\enubox{22 How long, ye simple ones, will ye love simplicity? and the scorners delight in their scorning, and fools hate knowledge?}

\enubox{23 Turn you at my reproof: behold, I will pour out my spirit unto you, I will make known my words unto you.}

\enubox{24 Because I have called, and ye refused; I have stretched out my hand, and no man regarded;}

\enubox{25 But ye have set at nought all my counsel, and would none of my reproof:}

\enubox{26 I also will laugh at your calamity; I will mock when your fear cometh;}

\enubox{27 When your fear cometh as desolation, and your destruction cometh as a whirlwind; when distress and anguish cometh upon you.}

\enubox{28 Then shall they call upon me, but I will not answer; they shall seek me early, but they shall not find me:}

\enubox{29 For that they hated knowledge, and did not choose the fear of the LORD:}

\enubox{30 They would none of my counsel: they despised all my reproof.}

\enubox{31 Therefore shall they eat of the fruit of their own way, and be filled with their own devices.}

\enubox{32 For the turning away of the simple shall slay them, and the prosperity of fools shall destroy them.}

\enubox{33 But whoso hearkeneth unto me shall dwell safely, and shall be quiet from fear of evil.}

\begin{center}
\enubox{\bf Chapter 2}
M517x530S15a48484x471S16d40499x475S22b04501x500 M508x515S10e00493x485 
\end{center}


\enubox{1 My son, if thou wilt receive my words, and hide my commandments with thee;}

\enubox{2 So that thou incline thine ear unto wisdom, and apply thine heart to understanding;}

\enubox{3 Yea, if thou criest after knowledge, and liftest up thy voice for understanding;}

\enubox{4 If thou seekest her as silver, and searchest for her as for hid treasures;}

\enubox{5 Then shalt thou understand the fear of the LORD, and find the knowledge of God.}

\enubox{6 For the LORD giveth wisdom: out of his mouth cometh knowledge and understanding.}

\enubox{7 He layeth up sound wisdom for the righteous: he is a buckler to them that walk uprightly.}

\enubox{8 He keepeth the paths of judgment, and preserveth the way of his saints.}

\enubox{9 Then shalt thou understand righteousness, and judgment, and equity; yea, every good path.}

\enubox{10 When wisdom entereth into thine heart, and knowledge is pleasant unto thy soul;}

\enubox{11 Discretion shall preserve thee, understanding shall keep thee:}

\enubox{12 To deliver thee from the way of the evil man, from the man that speaketh froward things;}

\enubox{13 Who leave the paths of uprightness, to walk in the ways of darkness;}

\enubox{14 Who rejoice to do evil, and delight in the frowardness of the wicked;}

\enubox{15 Whose ways are crooked, and they froward in their paths:}

\enubox{16 To deliver thee from the strange woman, even from the stranger which flattereth with her words;}

\enubox{17 Which forsaketh the guide of her youth, and forgetteth the covenant of her God.}

\enubox{18 For her house inclineth unto death, and her paths unto the dead.}

\enubox{19 None that go unto her return again, neither take they hold of the paths of life.}

\enubox{20 That thou mayest walk in the way of good men, and keep the paths of the righteous.}

\enubox{21 For the upright shall dwell in the land, and the perfect shall remain in it.}

\enubox{22 But the wicked shall be cut off from the earth, and the transgressors shall be rooted out of it.}

\begin{center}
\enubox{\bf Chapter 3}

\end{center}


\enubox{1 My son, forget not my law; but let thine heart keep my commandments:}

\enubox{2 For length of days, and long life, and peace, shall they add to thee.}

\enubox{3 Let not mercy and truth forsake thee: bind them about thy neck; write them upon the table of thine heart:}

\enubox{4 So shalt thou find favour and good understanding in the sight of God and man.}

\enubox{5 Trust in the LORD with all thine heart; and lean not unto thine own understanding.}

\enubox{6 In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths.}

\enubox{7 Be not wise in thine own eyes: fear the LORD, and depart from evil.}

\enubox{8 It shall be health to thy navel, and marrow to thy bones.}

\enubox{9 Honour the LORD with thy substance, and with the firstfruits of all thine increase:}

\enubox{10 So shall thy barns be filled with plenty, and thy presses shall burst out with new wine.}

\enubox{11 My son, despise not the chastening of the LORD; neither be weary of his correction:}

\enubox{12 For whom the LORD loveth he correcteth; even as a father the son in whom he delighteth.}

\enubox{13 Happy is the man that findeth wisdom, and the man that getteth understanding.}

\enubox{14 For the merchandise of it is better than the merchandise of silver, and the gain thereof than fine gold.}

\enubox{15 She is more precious than rubies: and all the things thou canst desire are not to be compared unto her.}

\enubox{16 Length of days is in her right hand; and in her left hand riches and honour.}

\enubox{17 Her ways are ways of pleasantness, and all her paths are peace.}

\enubox{18 She is a tree of life to them that lay hold upon her: and happy is every one that retaineth her.}

\enubox{19 The LORD by wisdom hath founded the earth; by understanding hath he established the heavens.}

\enubox{20 By his knowledge the depths are broken up, and the clouds drop down the dew.}

\enubox{21 My son, let not them depart from thine eyes: keep sound wisdom and discretion:}

\enubox{22 So shall they be life unto thy soul, and grace to thy neck.}

\enubox{23 Then shalt thou walk in thy way safely, and thy foot shall not stumble.}

\enubox{24 When thou liest down, thou shalt not be afraid: yea, thou shalt lie down, and thy sleep shall be sweet.}

\enubox{25 Be not afraid of sudden fear, neither of the desolation of the wicked, when it cometh.}

\enubox{26 For the LORD shall be thy confidence, and shall keep thy foot from being taken.}

\enubox{27 Withhold not good from them to whom it is due, when it is in the power of thine hand to do it.}

\enubox{28 Say not unto thy neighbour, Go, and come again, and to morrow I will give; when thou hast it by thee.}

\enubox{29 Devise not evil against thy neighbour, seeing he dwelleth securely by thee.}

\enubox{30 Strive not with a man without cause, if he have done thee no harm.}

\enubox{31 Envy thou not the oppressor, and choose none of his ways.}

\enubox{32 For the froward is abomination to the LORD: but his secret is with the righteous.}

\enubox{33 The curse of the LORD is in the house of the wicked: but he blesseth the habitation of the just.}

\enubox{34 Surely he scorneth the scorners: but he giveth grace unto the lowly.}

\enubox{35 The wise shall inherit glory: but shame shall be the promotion of fools.}
